>Description:
In the preference box, the option "reuse existing frames when opening new files" and the option "open files in separate tabs (not separate windows)" are not actually two different options. If you click both you get a third behavior where files opens in the current tab.

This should be changed to a combo box listing the three behaviors.  The wording also needs to be changed. Currently the words used are not parallel: reuse vs open, frames vs window.
